\chapter{Introduction}
\section{General Introduction}
In recent days network technology is developing rapidly and the network security is important issue. Amongst various security threats that have evolved lately, Denial of service (DoS) attack is most destructive according to the security experts. A Denial of Service attack is a method of blocking service from its intended users. The severity of this attack varies with the magnitude of loss and the duration of attack. DoS attacks could be extended to Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks which does damage in a massive scale. DDoS consists of many systems that work together to launch a much powerful attack [1].

\section{Problem statement}
Today’s world is facing problem of Denial-of-Service (DoS) attack in internet, organization, infrastructure etc. Therefore there is need to detect DoS attack.
The problem is detection of Denial-of-Service attack in network traffic. Hence work focuses on
\begin{enumerate}
\item To monitor the network traffic for generating basic features and find out correlations between two distinct features from the generated features using multivariate correlation analysis.
\item To classify Denial of Service attack from legitimate traffic.

\end{enumerate}

\section{Objectives}
\begin{enumerate}
\item To provide detection against denial-of-service attack.
\item To use the most sophisticated technique for detection of denial of service attacks.
\item To improve the performance of detection system.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Scope}

\begin{enumerate}
\item Increase the efficiency of computing systems by effective detection.
\item Effective detection of DoS attack makes legitimate user to access the online services and also provide the solution to improve performance of server.

\end{enumerate}

\section{Dissertation outline}
%

In next chapter, I have presented the review of literature surveyed during the completion of this dissertation.Chapter 3 and 4 are about Denial of service attack and Intrusion detection system respectively. Chapter 5 system architecture. Rest part focusses on the system design and evaluation. Out of which Chapter 6 is about requirement specifications, data flow and UML diagrams. Chapter 7 presents results and evaluation. Finally Chapter 8 concludes this report.

%%%%%%%%%%  CHAPTER 2 %%%%%%%%%%
\chapter{Literature Survey}
%
In today’s world, in the literature of computer network, the Information Security has become the one of the critical issue. Day by day more and more attacks are launched. The tools available for attacking are more powerful and are available freely on the Internet. Therefore it becomes necessary to provide more powerful tools for ensuring the security of the Information. Traditional IDS which was proposed in 80’s was the best solution for security at that time. But now it is become more necessary to improve the ability of IDS to detect more and more attacks. In addition to intrusion detection IDS should take some decisions by its own to prevent hacking of the data. Today’s IDS also support this feature so they are known as Intrusion Detection Systems.

	The security experts are trying to achieve more security by improving the Intrusion Detection System in many ways. Basically, there are two types of Intrusion Detection System; Network based Intrusion Detection system which detects unusual traffic flows and Host-based Intrusion Detection System which are responsible for monitoring single machine events for malicious activities.The literature consists of various methods for intrusion classification and detection. I surveyed following methods:	
\section{surveyed classification techniques}

\subsection{K-NN (k-Nearest Neighbor)}

K-nearest neighbor is one of the simple classification techniques. It determines the distance between data points on input vectors and unlabeled data points are assigned to its nearest neighbor. In this technique k is important parameter. When the value of k is 1, then the object is assigned to class of its nearest neighbor. If value of k is large, then it takes more time for prediction and affects the accuracy by reducing effect of noise. It requires large storage for larger dataset [29].

The advantages are simple, analytically tractable. Disadvantages are large storage requirements, lazy learner. In the k-NN underlying structure of the data is not identified.

\subsection{SVM(support vector machine)}
The support vector machine is used for classification and prediction. It is supervised learning algorithm. In this method hyper plane is used to separate data points. It is binary classifier so it separates data points into two classes +1 and -1.The normal data and suspicious data is represented by +1 and -1 respectively[30]. The line which separates dataset into two classes is separating hyperplane and points closest to the hyperplane are support vectors. The advantages are easy to interpret results, efficient. In case of two object classification, it gets superior performance. It handles only binary classification is the drawback of support vector machine.
\subsection{Naive Bayes}

Naive bayes is based on probability. According to membership probability it predicts the class. It analyzes the relation between dependent and independent variable to derive the conditional probability.
 The bayes theorem is:

    P (H/X) = P(X/H).P (H)/P(X)

Where, X represents the data record and H is hypothesis. The prior probability is represented by P (H).The P(X/H) and P (H/X) are the posterior probability of X and H respectively, conditioned on H and X respectively [29].

The advantage is easy to implement. It may be employed on larger data points but increases the time complexity. The assumptions of conditional independence, need of probability data are disadvantages of this technique.

\subsection{Decision Tree}
It is one of the commonly used classification techniques.  Binary classification tree is created in decision tree. Each node in tree represents binary predicate on one attribute. One branch in the tree corresponds to positive instance of predicate and other corresponds to negative instance of the predicate. There are various decision tree algorithms in the literature.

Domain knowledge is not required for tree construction is advantage of decision tree. The data mining expert with little knowledge of networking can construct decision tree models. Another advantage is learned results are easy for understanding.
Disadvantages are decision tree models in case of numeric dataset are complex, decision tree algorithms are unstable [31].

\textbf{RESULTS AND DISCUSSION}\\
We used Kddcup99 dataset[34]to check performance of various classification techniques. Dataset contains smurf, Neptune, teardrop, pod etc records of dos attack. The kdd dataset is modified with 110627 instances and 13 attributes. We used weka tool to compare various classification techniques. For this purpose dataset is used in ARFF format. The ARFF means attribure relation file format.

