%%%%%%%%%%  CHAPTER 5  %%%%%%%%%%
\chapter{System Architecture}
%
The system consists of two main phases i.e. training phase and test phase, as shown in fig.2. In the training phase normal profiles are determined and test phase consists of classification of attack. The whole detection process is described below:\\

Initially collect the dataset and preprocess on the dataset. Then generate the basic features of the dataset for individual record. After feature generation determine the multivariate correlation of these features using triangle area technique.
\begin{figure}[h!]
\centering
 %Requires \usepackage{graphicx}
\includegraphics[width=0.7\textwidth]{framework1}\\
\caption{Framework for Denial of Service attack detection}
\end{figure}

Triangle areas are used for extracting the correlation information between the features of traffic record and extracted correlations are stored in the triangle area maps (TAM). Multivariate correlation analysis is for characterization of network traffic.Triangle area technique is used to speed up the MCA (multivariate correlation analysis) process. Data transformation obtain triangle formed by the two features. In this technique, consider them as two images are symmetric along the main diagonals while comparing two TAMs. In Triangle area technique if any differences found in the lower triangles can be found in upper triangle also. So use either lower triangle or upper triangles of triangle area map. The MCA method has several advantages, the proposed triangle area based MCA is not vulnerable to linear change of all the features. It performs characterization of individual network traffic. Geometrical structure analysis reveals the correlations between two distinct features. If any anomaly behavior appears in the network then changes occur in the correlations. The results of Triangle area based MCA (multivariate correlation analysis) is given to the last step i.e. attack detection step for decision making. 	\\
		
The last step is to detect attack. In this step multivariate correlation analysis is applied to the SVM classification technique for making decision. The attack detection phase consists of “training set” and “test set” for different types of legitimate traffic records and individual observed traffic records respectively. These sets are used while making the decision about legitimate and attack. SVM uses the line to separate the dataset known as separating hyperplane. Hyperplane is decision boundary in which one side belongs to one class and other side belongs to another class. The points closest to the separating hyperplane are support vectors. To find the point closest to the hyperplane i.e. support vectors and the hyperplane must be far away from these support vectors. This is called as margin. The SVM classification algorithm makes decision and gives result as attack or normal. Finally compare the results.

